==Demographics==
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were three people, two households, and one family residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 1.6 people per square mile (0.6/km{{sup|2}}). There were two housing units at an average density of 1.1/sq&nbsp;mi (0.4/km{{sup|2}}). All residents were white and between forty-five and sixty-four. The median age was sixty-three years.

One household was a married couple living together, while the other was a male individual.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $41,250, and the median income for a family was $41,250. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $21,050.

